<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Containing Blocks - Containing block is formed by the padding edge of ancestor</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#containing-block-details" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="If the ancestor is not inline-level and is postioned absolute, the containing block is formed by the padding edge of the ancestor." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                position: absolute;
                display: block;
                background: red;
                border: solid 3px black;
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                position: absolute;
                padding-bottom: 10px;
                padding-right: 10px;
                background: green;
                width: 90px;
                height: 90px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>